Bill Romanowski calls Cam Newton 'boy' after Super Bowl loss

   By Sid Saraf Feb 7, 2016 at 11:38p ET
   0
   Shares

   Sunday wasn't [87]Cam Newton's day.

   The [88]Carolina Panthers quarterback got smacked around by the Denver
   Broncos defense in a 24-10 loss in Super Bowl 50. After the game, the
   criticisms started coming in droves.

   People had problems with Newton's turnovers, maybe his [89]effort level
   on a fumble, and for his [90]attitude at his postgame press conference.
   Then there was ex-NFL linebacker Bill Romanowski.

   This is what Romanowski had to say to Cam via a tweet that has since
   been deleted:
   [fs-load-module] Bill Romanowski via Twitter

   Later, Romanowski apologized.

     I apologize for that remark 'boy'. It was not intentional or even
     trying to disrespect others. Peace everyone.
     — Bill Romanowski (@billromanowski) [91]February 8, 2016

   Criticize Newton all you want. Don't call him "boy."


   0
   Shares
